addNominee(uint256,address,uint256).details: shares is compared with total shares issued in a staking to see the percent nominee can withdraw. Nominee can withdraw only after one year past the end of tenure of staking. Upto 1 year past the end of tenure of staking, owner can withdraw principle amount of staking as well as can CRUD nominees. Owner of staking is has this time to withdraw their staking, if they fail to do so, after that nominees are allowed to withdraw. Withdrawl by first nominee will trigger staking into nomination mode and owner of staking cannot withdraw the principle amount as it will be distributed with only nominees and only they can withdraw it.

params._nomineeAddress: - address of nominee to be added to staking
params._shares: - amount of shares of the staking to the nominee

params._stakingPlanId: - rewardee can choose plan while claiming rewards as stakings

params._loanMonths: - number of months or duration of loan, loan taker must repay the loan before this period
params._loanRate: - this is total % of loaning amount charged while taking loan, this charge is sent to luckpool in NRT manager which ends up distributed back to the community again

params._fractionFrom15: - NRT fraction (max 15%) benefit to be given to user. rest is sent back to NRT in Luck Pool
params._isUrgentLoanAllowed: - if urgent loan is not allowed then staker can take loan only after 75% of time elapsed
params._months: - is number of staking months of a plan. for eg. 12 months

getCurrentMonth().return: current month is the TimeAlly month

params._addresses: - array of address to send rewards
params._exaEsAmountArray: - array of ExaES amounts sent to each address of _addresses with same index

params._atMonth: - particular month to check staking active

isStakingActive(address,uint256,uint256).return: true is staking is in correct time frame and also no loan on it

params._exaEsAmount: - amount of ES tokens (in 18 decimals thats why 'exa') that user wishes to stake

repayLoanSelf(uint256).details: need to give allowance before this

params._months: - array of months user is interested to see benefits.

seeBenefitOfAStakingByMonths(address,uin.return: amount of ExaES of benefits of entered months

params._loanPlanId: - the loan plan user wishes to take loan.
params._stakingIds: - array of staking ids which should be used to estimate max loan amount

params._exaEsAmount: - loan amount, this will also be the loan repay amount, the interest will first be deducted from this and then amount will be credited
params._loanPlanId: - user can select this plan which defines loan duration and loan interest
params._stakingIds: - staking ids user wishes to encash for taking the loan

params._exaEsAmount: - amount to add to your rewards for sending rewards to others

params._months: - array of months user is interested to withdraw benefits of staking.

methods.constructor: sets up TimeAlly contract when deployed

createLoanPlan(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: this function is used by owner to create plans for new loans

newStaking(uint256,uint256).notice: takes ES from user and locks it for a time according to plan selected by user

viewNomination(address,uint256,address).notice: this function is used to read the nomination of a nominee address of a staking of a user

withdrawBenefitOfAStakingByMonths(uint25.notice: this function is used for withdrawing the benefits of a staking of any user
